omatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΟΔΑ[...\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>The people (of Tyndaris ...)\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Gentili speculatively read this as a reference to an individual called Aristodamos or Kleodamos, but as Robert already observed, this must, surely, as in ISic003348, be a reference to the damos (and was so restored by Manganaro). As with ISic003348 it was found in re-use in a late antique element of the fortification walls.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1953.0277 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gentili 1952 164 no.1821 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001959\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001959\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1965 203 no.1 tav.72.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 58 no.4 fig.22 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  